<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1017,142,203]" box="[160,409,142,168]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1017,142,203]" box="[160,1017,178,203]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">Body elongate, narrow, black or brown in colour, rear tail darker. Foot large.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="293" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1155,255,350]" box="[160,252,255,281]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1155,255,350]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">Specimens found grazing on biofouling at night over calcarean red algae or boulders, in very superficial waters.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="293" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1155,403,498]" box="[160,300,403,429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1155,403,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
Atlantic Spanish coast: Canary Islands and Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[760,857,438,463]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[873,1095,438,463]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and Mediterranean Spanish coast: Catalonia (this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="293" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[159,1154,551,715]" box="[160,262,551,577]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[159,1154,551,715]" pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
This species is rarely observed and very small. Easily distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName pageId="28" pageNumber="293">
